<h3>OctoDash Setup</h3>

<h4>Welcome to OctoDash v3!</h4>

<p>
  You can view OctoDash <a href="/plugin/octodash/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a>.
  If you are running OctoPrint on a Raspberry Pi (or other Debian-based system) with a display connected, you can use the OctoDash-provided script to configure
  it to open OctoDash on boot. To copy the script into your home directory, click the button below.
  Once copied, connect to your system via either SSH or a keyboard and run the script.

</p>
<p>
  If you have an existing installation of legacy OctoDash, the script will detect that and make
  the necessary changes to launch OctoDash v3 instead.
</p>
<button data-bind="click: copyScript, enable: !copyInProgress()" class="btn">Copy script</button>
<div data-bind="if: configPaths().length">
  <h4>Config Setup</h4>
  <p>
    An existing legacy OctoDash config was found on your system at the following location.
    Would you like to migrate it?
  </p>
  <ul data-bind="foreach: configPaths">
    <li><code data-bind="text: $data" ></code><button class="btn" data-bind="click: $parent.migrate, enable: !$parent.migrateInProgress()">Migrate</button></li>
  </ul>
</div>
<!-- ko if:  configPaths.length === 0-->
<div class="plugins-chosen" data-bind="if: singlePlugins().length">
  <h4>Plugins Found</h4>
  <p>The following pluigns were detected and will be used in OctoDash. You can disable this behavior in the plugin settings</p>
  <ul data-bind="foreach: singlePlugins">
    <li><code data-bind="text: $data"></code></li>
  </ul>
</div>
<div class="filament-chosen" data-bind="if: filamentPlugins().length === 1">
 <h4>Filament Chosen</h4>
 <p>The plugin <code data-bind="text: filamentPlugins()[0]"></code> was detected an enabled in OctoDash. You can disable it in the plugin settings.</p>
</div>
<div data-bind="if: filamentPlugins().length" class="filament-choices">
  <h4>Multiple filament plugins available</h4>
  <p>The following filament pluigns were detected installed. You can enable one in the plugin settings.</p>
  <ul data-bind="foreach: filamentPlugins">
    <li><code data-bind="text: $data"></code></li>
  </ul>
</div>
<div class="power-chosen" data-bind="if: powerPlugins().length === 1">
 <h4>Power Chosen</h4>
 <p>The plugin <code data-bind="text: powerPlugins()[0]"></code> was detected and enabled in OctoDash for controling the printer power state. You can disable it in the plugin settings.</p>
</div>
<div data-bind="if: powerPlugins().length" class="power-choices">
  <h4>Multiple power plugins available</h4>
  <p>The following power management pluigns were detected installed. You can enable one for use with OctoDash in the plugin settings.</p>
  <ul data-bind="foreach: powerPlugins">
    <li><code data-bind="text: $data"></code></li>
  </ul>
</div>
